<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I don't buy it</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack">TheBlack</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:53 p.m. 21/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I don't buy it<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1936" TARGET=_self>Re: Apology to CC</A> (Keira {BC})
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I've been playing since 0.5 and it's just not possible to level that quickly without taking some short cuts. I watched the power gamers at work throughout the development of the game. Even using rain spells in dungeons back when that was possible they were hard pressed to get into the low 30s after 1.5 months of playing. These are guys that played every day non-stop.
<P>I strongly suspect that anyone who has 40+ level characters at this stage was using some serious MOB trapping exploits.
<P>There were also a bunch of players exploiting a platinum duplicating bug (for lack of a better term) and a bunch of them have already been kicked out of the game. Having unlimited wealth would help one level faster, but even that would not explain 40+ in a month.
<P>Oh well, it really doesn't matter to me if someone reaches level 50 in four weeks. With the +/- 4 level limit they won't be bothering me at all.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
